      From the manufacturer

      Sony MDR-ZX310AP

      ZX Series Wired On Ear Headphones with mic

      Sound meets style for life on the go. More than your basic pair of over-the-head headphones, the Sony MDR-ZX310AP headset delivers rock-solid audio performance with an integrated microphone.

      Microphone Integrated microphone and multi-function control button
      Quality Sound The large 30mm driver units coupled with ferrite magnets will accurately reproduce a broad, dynamic frequency range.
      Swivel Earcups The slim, swivel and folding style earcups stow away for compact portability.
      Pressure Relieving Earpads The lightweight, adjustable headband with swivel ear pads is designed for comfort so you can enjoy extended listening sessions without fatigue.
      Y-Type cord The traditional Y-type cord design helps reduce the chance of tangles while the 4-conductor gold plated, L-shaped plug ensures a good connection.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Amazon Customer
      5 out of 5 stars
      Long lasting functionality
      NOTE: The attached pictures are of my (six year old) pair. I bought an identical pair (same brand, color, etc) a few years back when I graduated high school. I really liked them and they are an affordable price, so I bought this pair for my sister. My pair has worked well all these years and still provides excellent sound quality. It has been almost six years and they are just now starting to wear. The ear cushions are tearing off and a tiny bit of the paint is beginning to chip - and this is after almost daily use for five and a half years and carrying them around in my backpack half the time. I personally don't mind the tearing as they still hold together well enough and I don't notice the tearing when wearing the headphones - the cushion itself is still good. The mic still works great and so does the sound functionality. I imagine they will last many more years to come. These headphones are adjustable and the ears are even labeled: "R" for "Right ear"; "L" for "Left ear".
